dc_title_s: The road from London to York / drawn & engrav'd by J. Gibson.
dc_description_s: Map of a road from London to York via Stamford, Grantham, Newark-on-Trent, and Doncaster, depicted in ten narrow strips. Shows cities and towns, mile markers, rivers, and road junctions. Relief shown pictorially. North orientation varies. North arrows not shown. Map detached from: The gentleman's magazine, and historical chronicle. Volume XXXVI: for the year M.CDD.LXVI. London: Printed for D. Henry and R. Cave, [1766]. Map was originally published in the June 1766 issue. "Gent:Mag". Includes note. Scale approximately 1:320,000.
